“I watched my parents cry with joy that I could vote, but now we have nothing to do,” he said.
Despite achieving a vital but close victory in the regional elections of December last year, Catalan pro-independent parties tried to keep up this year, many of the most well-known leaders are either in exile and refereeing to their own exile, or in detention.
Joan Puig, a 42-year-old mechanic who recorded the protest on his phone in support of police, said politicians on both sides fueled the conflict.
