He wanted to prove that he was “someone,” he said, so that he wouldn’t disappoint everyone when they finally find out about his sexuality.
The winner of two bronze medals at the Olympics has become a well-known supporter of LGBT campaigns and has taken advantage of his appearance at this year’s Commonwealth Games in Australia to demand more countries to decriminalize homosexuality.
