The F125 frigate was discussed in the press last year when the German Navy officially refused to take the ship and returned it to the Blohm & Voss shipyard in Hamburg.
This was the first time that the Navy returned a ship to the builder after delivery.
Not much information is available about the reasons for the refusal, but the German media cited a number of crucial "software and hardware defects" that would have made the warship useless in a combat mission.
The software flaws were important in particular because the Baden-Wuerttemberg-class vessels will be operated by a crew of about 120 sailors, only half of the crews on the older Bremen-class frigates.
